                            {
                                "template": "header",
                                "options": {
                                    "text": "Message from the Head"
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "template": "content",
                                "options": {
                                    "text": "With much of our community engaged in summer plans away from Silicon Valley, we wanted to keep families and alumni up to date on the transformation happening on our Saratoga campus. As you know, we’ve started construction of a new gym and theater at our upper school. The old adage, “You have to crack an egg to make an omelet” certainly applies, and we are deep into the egg-cracking phase.
                                        <br>
                                        <br>
                                        Although it’s very exciting to see the project underway, we still need more support – support from everyone in our community – to complete it. We all need to do our part to pitch in and make a contribution, and we hope you will help us get this done.
                                        <br>
                                        <br>
                                        Read on and click through for more news, photos and video, and enjoy your summer!
                                        <br>
                                        <br>
                                        Chris Nikoloff<br>
                                        Head of School
                                        "
                                }
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "template": "grid",
            "options": {
                "columns": [
                    {
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "template": "header",
                                "options": {
                                    "text": "Why a gym and theater?"
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "template": "content",
                                "options": {
                                    "text": "At Harker our students are learning and doing, to make a difference in the world. While the classroom is where the bulk of academic learning takes place, an education for the whole child encompasses more than academics. Students develop many of the qualities that enable them to make a difference – confidence, perseverance, integrity and more – in our extracurricular programs such as athletics and performing arts. And we don’t have adequate facilities for these programs on our upper school campus.
                                        <br>
                                        <br>
                                        In addition to supporting athletics and performing arts specifically, the new gym and theater will provide gathering spaces for the entire student body (for school meetings or other events) and for other student programs (such as debate, science research, alumni reunions and more). Our whole community of students, parents, faculty and alumni will be able to experience the benefits of these new facilities.

                                        "
                                }
                            }
                        ]
